/*!
    \page kdgpu-examples KDGpu Examples

    \brief A collection of examples demonstrating Vulkan rendering techniques and features using KDGpu.

    These examples are organized by complexity, from basic triangle rendering to advanced techniques like ray tracing and order-independent transparency. Most examples use the \subpage kdgpuexample_helper "KDGpuExample Helper API" to reduce boilerplate and focus on the specific technique being demonstrated.

    Examples assume you understand basic 3D graphics concepts (vertices, shaders, coordinate systems, matrix math, texture sampling, depth testing) but not necessarily Vulkan-specific APIs.

    \section beginner_examples Beginner Examples

    These examples introduce fundamental rendering concepts and the KDGpu API. Start here if you're new to KDGpu or Vulkan.

    - \subpage hello_triangle - Your first triangle using the KDGpuExample helper API
    - \subpage hello_triangle_native - Raw KDGpu API showing all initialization steps without helper abstractions
    - \subpage hello_triangle_hlsl - Using HLSL shaders instead of GLSL with DXC compilation
    - \subpage hello_triangle_slang - Using Slang shaders instead of GLSL with Slang compilation
    - \subpage textured_quad - Texture loading, sampling, and applying textures to geometry
    - \subpage hello_triangle_overlap - Triple-buffered rendering with fence synchronization for frame overlap
    - \subpage hello_triangle_apple - Platform-specific initialization for macOS using MoltenVK

    \section intermediate_examples Intermediate Examples

    These examples demonstrate multi-pass rendering, anti-aliasing, compute shaders, and descriptor management.

    \subsection msaa_examples Multi-Sample Anti-Aliasing (MSAA)
    - \subpage hello_triangle_msaa - Multi-sample anti-aliasing for smooth edges
    - \subpage hello_triangle_msaa_dynamic_rendering - MSAA with VK_KHR_dynamic_rendering extension

    \subsection multipass_examples Multi-Pass Rendering
    - \subpage render_to_texture - Off-screen rendering to texture for multi-pass effects
    - \subpage render_to_texture_subpass - Efficient subpass-based rendering for tile-based GPUs
    - \subpage render_to_texture_subpass_dynamic_rendering - Subpasses with dynamic rendering
    - \subpage depth_texture_lookup - Sampling depth textures in shaders for advanced effects
    - \subpage depth_bias - Depth bias for shadow mapping and z-fighting prevention

    \subsection ubo_compute_examples Uniform Buffers and Compute
    - \subpage dynamic_ubo - Dynamic uniform buffer offsets for efficient per-object data
    - \subpage compute_particles - GPU particle simulation using compute shaders
    - \subpage offscreen_rendering - Headless rendering to image files without a window

    \subsection descriptor_examples Descriptor Management
    - \subpage bindgroup_indexing - Descriptor array indexing with nonUniformEXT qualifier
    - \subpage bindgroup_partially_bound - Partially bound descriptor sets for flexible resource binding
    - \subpage host_image_copy_texture - Host-side image copying with VK_EXT_host_image_copy

    \subsection multiview_examples Multi-View Rendering
    - \subpage multiview - Multi-view rendering for VR and stereo rendering
    - \subpage multiview_stereo - Stereo swapchains for VR headsets and 3D displays

    \section advanced_examples Advanced Examples

    These examples showcase modern rendering techniques including mesh shaders, ray tracing, order-independent transparency, and XR.

    \subsection modern_pipeline_examples Modern Pipeline Features
    - \subpage hello_sphere_mesh - Mesh shaders for GPU-driven geometry generation
    - \subpage buffer_reference - GPU pointers with VK_KHR_buffer_device_address

    \subsection raytracing_examples Ray Tracing
    - \subpage hello_triangle_rt - Introduction to ray tracing with acceleration structures
    - \subpage hello_sphere_rt - Procedural geometry with ray tracing intersection shaders
    - \subpage hybrid_raster_rt - Hybrid rasterization and ray tracing pipeline

    \subsection advanced_rendering_examples Advanced Rendering Techniques
    - \subpage compute_oit_transparency - Order-independent transparency using per-pixel linked lists
    - \subpage wireframe_geometry - Single-pass wireframe rendering with barycentric coordinates

    \subsection xr_examples XR (Extended Reality)
    - \subpage hello_xr - OpenXR integration with compositor layers and passthrough
    - \subpage hello_xr_multiview - XR rendering with multi-view for efficient stereo rendering

    \section helper_info About the Helper API

    See \subpage kdgpuexample_helper for details about the KDGpuExample helper API used by most examples, and when to use the native API instead.
*/
